\frac{w}{d} = \frac{1024}{768} \implies w = \frac{1024d}{768}.
w^2+d^2 = 100^2.
w^2+d^2 = \left(\frac{1024}{768}\right)^2d^2+d^2 = 100^2,
\left[\left(\frac{1024}{768}\right)^2+1\right]d^2 = 10000.
d^2 = 3600 \implies d = 60 \textrm{in}
w = \frac{1024}{768}\cdot 60 \textrm{in} = 80 \textrm{in}.
